2840#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2841
2842/* Parse a format directive in function call described by INFO starting
2843 at STR and populate DIR structure. Bump up *ARGNO by the number of
2844 arguments extracted for the directive. Return the length of
2845 the directive. */
2846
2847static size_t
2848parse_directive (pass_sprintf_length::call_info &info,
2849 directive &dir, format_result *res,
2850 const char *str, unsigned *argno)
2851{
2852 const char *pcnt = strchr (str, '%');
2853 dir.beg = str;
2854
2855 if (size_t len = pcnt ? pcnt - str : *str ? strlen (str) : 1)
2856 {
2857 /* This directive is either a plain string or the terminating nul
2858 (which isn't really a directive but it simplifies things to
2859 handle it as if it were). */
2860 dir.len = len;
2861 dir.fmtfunc = format_plain;
2862
2863 if (dump_file)
2864 {
2865 fprintf (dump_file, " Directive %u at offset %llu: \"%.*s\", "
2866 "length = %llu\n",
2867 dir.dirno,
2868 (unsigned long long)(size_t)(dir.beg - info.fmtstr),
2869 (int)dir.len, dir.beg, (unsigned long long)dir.len);
2870 }
2871
2872 return len - !*str;
2873 }
2874
2875 const char *pf = pcnt + 1;
2876
2877 /* POSIX numbered argument index or zero when none. */
2878 unsigned dollar = 0;
2879
2880 /* With and precision. -1 when not specified, HOST_WIDE_INT_MIN
2881 when given by a va_list argument, and a non-negative value
2882 when specified in the format string itself. */
2883 HOST_WIDE_INT width = -1;
2884 HOST_WIDE_INT precision = -1;
2885
2886 /* Width specified via the asterisk. Need not be INTEGER_CST.
2887 For vararg functions set to void_node. */
2888 tree star_width = NULL_TREE;
2889
2890 /* Width specified via the asterisk. Need not be INTEGER_CST.
2891 For vararg functions set to void_node. */
2892 tree star_precision = NULL_TREE;
2893
2894 if (ISDIGIT (*pf))
2895 {
2896 /* This could be either a POSIX positional argument, the '0'
2897 flag, or a width, depending on what follows. Store it as
2898 width and sort it out later after the next character has
2899 been seen. */
2900 char *end;
2901 width = strtol (pf, &end, 10);
2902 pf = end;
2903 }
2904 else if ('*' == *pf)
2905 {
2906 /* Similarly to the block above, this could be either a POSIX
2907 positional argument or a width, depending on what follows. */
2908 if (*argno < gimple_call_num_args (info.callstmt))
2909 star_width = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, (*argno)++);
2910 else
2911 star_width = void_node;
2912 ++pf;
2913 }
2914
2915 if (*pf == '$')
2916 {
2917 /* Handle the POSIX dollar sign which references the 1-based
2918 positional argument number. */
2919 if (width != -1)
2920 dollar = width + info.argidx;
2921 else if (star_width
2922 && TREE_CODE (star_width) == INTEGER_CST
2923 && (TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (star_width))
2924 <= TYPE_PRECISION (integer_type_node)))
2925 dollar = width + tree_to_shwi (star_width);
2926
2927 /* Bail when the numbered argument is out of range (it will
2928 have already been diagnosed by -Wformat). */
2929 if (dollar == 0
2930 || dollar == info.argidx
2931 || dollar > gimple_call_num_args (info.callstmt))
2932 return false;
2933
2934 --dollar;
2935
2936 star_width = NULL_TREE;
2937 width = -1;
2938 ++pf;
2939 }
2940
2941 if (dollar || !star_width)
2942 {
2943 if (width != -1)
2944 {
2945 if (width == 0)
2946 {
2947 /* The '0' that has been interpreted as a width above is
2948 actually a flag. Reset HAVE_WIDTH, set the '0' flag,
2949 and continue processing other flags. */
2950 width = -1;
2951 dir.set_flag ('0');
2952 }
2953 else if (!dollar)
2954 {
2955 /* (Non-zero) width has been seen. The next character
2956 is either a period or a digit. */
2957 goto start_precision;
2958 }
2959 }
2960 /* When either '$' has been seen, or width has not been seen,
2961 the next field is the optional flags followed by an optional
2962 width. */
2963 for ( ; ; ) {
2964 switch (*pf)
2965 {
2966 case ' ':
2967 case '0':
2968 case '+':
2969 case '-':
2970 case '#':
2971 dir.set_flag (*pf++);
2972 break;
2973
2974 default:
2975 goto start_width;
2976 }
2977 }
2978
2979 start_width:
2980 if (ISDIGIT (*pf))
2981 {
2982 char *end;
2983 width = strtol (pf, &end, 10);
2984 pf = end;
2985 }
2986 else if ('*' == *pf)
2987 {
2988 if (*argno < gimple_call_num_args (info.callstmt))
2989 star_width = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, (*argno)++);
2990 else
2991 {
2992 /* This is (likely) a va_list. It could also be an invalid
2993 call with insufficient arguments. */
2994 star_width = void_node;
2995 }
2996 ++pf;
2997 }
2998 else if ('\'' == *pf)
2999 {
3000 /* The POSIX apostrophe indicating a numeric grouping
3001 in the current locale. Even though it's possible to
3002 estimate the upper bound on the size of the output
3003 based on the number of digits it probably isn't worth
3004 continuing. */
3005 return 0;
3006 }
3007 }
3008
3009 start_precision:
3010 if ('.' == *pf)
3011 {
3012 ++pf;
3013
3014 if (ISDIGIT (*pf))
3015 {
3016 char *end;
3017 precision = strtol (pf, &end, 10);
3018 pf = end;
3019 }
3020 else if ('*' == *pf)
3021 {
3022 if (*argno < gimple_call_num_args (info.callstmt))
3023 star_precision = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, (*argno)++);
3024 else
3025 {
3026 /* This is (likely) a va_list. It could also be an invalid
3027 call with insufficient arguments. */
3028 star_precision = void_node;
3029 }
3030 ++pf;
3031 }
3032 else
3033 {
3034 /* The decimal precision or the asterisk are optional.
3035 When neither is dirified it's taken to be zero. */
3036 precision = 0;
3037 }
3038 }
3039
3040 switch (*pf)
3041 {
3042 case 'h':
3043 if (pf[1] == 'h')
3044 {
3045 ++pf;
3046 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_hh;
3047 }
3048 else
3049 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_h;
3050 ++pf;
3051 break;
3052
3053 case 'j':
3054 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_j;
3055 ++pf;
3056 break;
3057
3058 case 'L':
3059 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_L;
3060 ++pf;
3061 break;
3062
3063 case 'l':
3064 if (pf[1] == 'l')
3065 {
3066 ++pf;
3067 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_ll;
3068 }
3069 else
3070 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_l;
3071 ++pf;
3072 break;
3073
3074 case 't':
3075 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_t;
3076 ++pf;
3077 break;
3078
3079 case 'z':
3080 dir.modifier = FMT_LEN_z;
3081 ++pf;
3082 break;
3083 }
3084
3085 switch (*pf)
3086 {
3087 /* Handle a sole '%' character the same as "%%" but since it's
3088 undefined prevent the result from being folded. */
3089 case '\0':
3090 --pf;
3091 res->range.min = res->range.max = HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U;
3092 /* FALLTHRU */
3093 case '%':
3094 dir.fmtfunc = format_percent;
3095 break;
3096
3097 case 'a':
3098 case 'A':
3099 case 'e':
3100 case 'E':
3101 case 'f':
3102 case 'F':
3103 case 'g':
3104 case 'G':
3105 res->floating = true;
3106 dir.fmtfunc = format_floating;
3107 break;
3108
3109 case 'd':
3110 case 'i':
3111 case 'o':
3112 case 'u':
3113 case 'x':
3114 case 'X':
3115 dir.fmtfunc = format_integer;
3116 break;
3117
3118 case 'p':
3119 /* The %p output is implementation-defined. It's possible
3120 to determine this format but due to extensions (edirially
3121 those of the Linux kernel -- see bug 78512) the first %p
3122 in the format string disables any further processing. */
3123 return false;
3124
3125 case 'n':
3126 /* %n has side-effects even when nothing is actually printed to
3127 any buffer. */
3128 info.nowrite = false;
3129 dir.fmtfunc = format_none;
3130 break;
3131
3132 case 'c':
3133 dir.fmtfunc = format_character;
3134 break;
3135
3136 case 'S':
3137 case 's':
3138 dir.fmtfunc = format_string;
3139 break;
3140
3141 default:
3142 /* Unknown conversion specification. */
3143 return 0;
3144 }
3145
3146 dir.specifier = *pf++;
3147
3148 if (star_width)
3149 {
3150 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (star_width)))
3151 dir.set_width (star_width);
3152 else
3153 {
3154 /* Width specified by a va_list takes on the range [0, -INT_MIN]
3155 (width is the absolute value of that specified). */
3156 dir.width[0] = 0;
3157 dir.width[1] = target_int_max () + 1;
3158 }
3159 }
3160 else
3161 dir.set_width (width);
3162
3163 if (star_precision)
3164 {
3165 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (star_precision)))
3166 dir.set_precision (star_precision);
3167 else
3168 {
3169 /* Precision specified by a va_list takes on the range [-1, INT_MAX]
3170 (unlike width, negative precision is ignored). */
3171 dir.prec[0] = -1;
3172 dir.prec[1] = target_int_max ();
3173 }
3174 }
3175 else
3176 dir.set_precision (precision);
3177
3178 /* Extract the argument if the directive takes one and if it's
3179 available (e.g., the function doesn't take a va_list). Treat
3180 missing arguments the same as va_list, even though they will
3181 have likely already been diagnosed by -Wformat. */
3182 if (dir.specifier != '%'
3183 && *argno < gimple_call_num_args (info.callstmt))
3184 dir.arg = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, dollar ? dollar : (*argno)++);
3185
3186 /* Return the length of the format directive. */
3187 dir.len = pf - pcnt;
3188
3189 if (dump_file)
3190 {
3191 fprintf (dump_file, " Directive %u at offset %llu: \"%.*s\"",
3192 dir.dirno, (unsigned long long)(size_t)(dir.beg - info.fmtstr),
3193 (int)dir.len, dir.beg);
3194 if (star_width)
3195 {
3196 if (dir.width[0] == dir.width[1])
3197 fprintf (dump_file, ", width = %lli", (long long)dir.width[0]);
3198 else
3199 fprintf (dump_file, ", width in range [%lli, %lli]",
3200 (long long)dir.width[0], (long long)dir.width[1]);
3201 }
3202
3203 if (star_precision)
3204 {
3205 if (dir.prec[0] == dir.prec[1])
3206 fprintf (dump_file, ", precision = %lli", (long long)dir.prec[0]);
3207 else
3208 fprintf (dump_file, ", precision in range [%lli, %lli]",
3209 (long long)dir.prec[0], (long long)dir.prec[1]);
3210 }
3211 fputc ('\n', dump_file);
3212 }
3213
3214 return dir.len;
3215}
3216
3217/* Compute the length of the output resulting from the call to a formatted
3218 output function described by INFO and store the result of the call in
3219 *RES. Issue warnings for detected past the end writes. Return true
3220 if the complete format string has been processed and *RES can be relied
3221 on, false otherwise (e.g., when a unknown or unhandled directive was seen
3222 that caused the processing to be terminated early). */
3223
3224bool
3225pass_sprintf_length::compute_format_length (call_info &info,
3226 format_result *res)
3227{
3228 if (dump_file)
3229 {
3230 location_t callloc = gimple_location (info.callstmt);
3231 fprintf (dump_file, "%s:%i: ",
3232 LOCATION_FILE (callloc), LOCATION_LINE (callloc));
3233 print_generic_expr (dump_file, info.func, dump_flags);
3234
3235 fprintf (dump_file, ": objsize = %llu, fmtstr = \"%s\"\n",
3236 (unsigned long long)info.objsize, info.fmtstr);
3237 }
3238
3239 /* Reset the minimum and maximum byte counters. */
3240 res->range.min = res->range.max = 0;
3241
3242 /* No directive has been seen yet so the length of output is bounded
3243 by the known range [0, 0] (with no conversion producing more than
3244 4K bytes) until determined otherwise. */
3245 res->knownrange = true;
3246 res->under4k = true;
3247 res->floating = false;
3248 res->warned = false;
3249
3250 /* 1-based directive counter. */
3251 unsigned dirno = 1;
3252
3253 /* The variadic argument counter. */
3254 unsigned argno = info.argidx;
3255
3256 for (const char *pf = info.fmtstr; ; ++dirno)
3257 {
3258 directive dir = directive ();
3259 dir.dirno = dirno;
3260
3261 size_t n = parse_directive (info, dir, res, pf, &argno);
3262
3263 /* Return failure if the format function fails. */
3264 if (!format_directive (info, res, dir))
3265 return false;
3266
3267 /* Return success the directive is zero bytes long and it's
3268 the last think in the format string (i.e., it's the terminating
3269 nul, which isn't really a directive but handling it as one makes
3270 things simpler). */
3271 if (!n)
3272 return *pf == '\0';
3273
3274 pf += n;
3275 }
3276
3277 /* The complete format string was processed (with or without warnings). */
3278 return true;
3279}

3281/* Return the size of the object referenced by the expression DEST if
3282 available, or -1 otherwise. */
3283
3284static unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT
3285get_destination_size (tree dest)
3286{
3287 /* Initialize object size info before trying to compute it. */
3288 init_object_sizes ();
3289
3290 /* Use __builtin_object_size to determine the size of the destination
3291 object. When optimizing, determine the smallest object (such as
3292 a member array as opposed to the whole enclosing object), otherwise
3293 use type-zero object size to determine the size of the enclosing
3294 object (the function fails without optimization in this type). */
3295 int ost = optimize > 0;
3296 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT size;
3297 if (compute_builtin_object_size (dest, ost, &size))
3298 return size;
3299
3300 return HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U;
3301}
3302
3303/* Given a suitable result RES of a call to a formatted output function
3304 described by INFO, substitute the result for the return value of
3305 the call. The result is suitable if the number of bytes it represents
3306 is known and exact. A result that isn't suitable for substitution may
3307 have its range set to the range of return values, if that is known.
3308 Return true if the call is removed and gsi_next should not be performed
3309 in the caller. */
3310
3311static bool
3312try_substitute_return_value (gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi,
3313 const pass_sprintf_length::call_info &info,
3314 const format_result &res)
3315{
3316 tree lhs = gimple_get_lhs (info.callstmt);
3317
3318 /* Set to true when the entire call has been removed. */
3319 bool removed = false;
3320
3321 /* The minimum return value. */
3322 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT minretval = res.range.min;
3323
3324 /* The maximum return value is in most cases bounded by RES.RANGE.MAX
3325 but in cases involving multibyte characters could be as large as
3326 RES.RANGE.UNLIKELY. */
3327 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT maxretval
3328 = res.range.unlikely < res.range.max ? res.range.max : res.range.unlikely;
3329
3330 /* Adjust the number of bytes which includes the terminating nul
3331 to reflect the return value of the function which does not.
3332 Because the valid range of the function is [INT_MIN, INT_MAX],
3333 a valid range before the adjustment below is [0, INT_MAX + 1]
3334 (the functions only return negative values on error or undefined
3335 behavior). */
3336 if (minretval <= target_int_max () + 1)
3337 --minretval;
3338 if (maxretval <= target_int_max () + 1)
3339 --maxretval;
3340
3341 /* Avoid the return value optimization when the behavior of the call
3342 is undefined either because any directive may have produced 4K or
3343 more of output, or the return value exceeds INT_MAX, or because
3344 the output overflows the destination object (but leave it enabled
3345 when the function is bounded because then the behavior is well-
3346 defined). */
3347 if (res.under4k
3348 && minretval == maxretval
3349 && (info.bounded || minretval < info.objsize)
3350 && minretval <= target_int_max ()
3351 /* Not prepared to handle possibly throwing calls here; they shouldn't
3352 appear in non-artificial testcases, except when the __*_chk routines
3353 are badly declared. */
3354 && !stmt_ends_bb_p (info.callstmt))
3355 {
3356 tree cst = build_int_cst (integer_type_node, minretval);
3357
3358 if (lhs == NULL_TREE
3359 && info.nowrite)
3360 {
3361 /* Remove the call to the bounded function with a zero size
3362 (e.g., snprintf(0, 0, "%i", 123)) if there is no lhs. */
3363 unlink_stmt_vdef (info.callstmt);
3364 gsi_remove (gsi, true);
3365 removed = true;
3366 }
3367 else if (info.nowrite)
3368 {
3369 /* Replace the call to the bounded function with a zero size
3370 (e.g., snprintf(0, 0, "%i", 123) with the constant result
3371 of the function. */
3372 if (!update_call_from_tree (gsi, cst))
3373 gimplify_and_update_call_from_tree (gsi, cst);
3374 gimple *callstmt = gsi_stmt (*gsi);
3375 update_stmt (callstmt);
3376 }
3377 else if (lhs)
3378 {
3379 /* Replace the left-hand side of the call with the constant
3380 result of the formatted function. */
3381 gimple_call_set_lhs (info.callstmt, NULL_TREE);
3382 gimple *g = gimple_build_assign (lhs, cst);
3383 gsi_insert_after (gsi, g, GSI_NEW_STMT);
3384 update_stmt (info.callstmt);
3385 }
3386
3387 if (dump_file)
3388 {
3389 if (removed)
3390 fprintf (dump_file, " Removing call statement.");
3391 else
3392 {
3393 fprintf (dump_file, " Substituting ");
3394 print_generic_expr (dump_file, cst, dump_flags);
3395 fprintf (dump_file, " for %s.\n",
3396 info.nowrite ? "statement" : "return value");
3397 }
3398 }
3399 }
3400 else if (lhs)
3401 {
3402 bool setrange = false;
3403
3404 if ((info.bounded || maxretval < info.objsize)
3405 && res.under4k
3406 && (minretval < target_int_max ()
3407 && maxretval < target_int_max ()))
3408 {
3409 /* If the result is in a valid range bounded by the size of
3410 the destination set it so that it can be used for subsequent
3411 optimizations. */
3412 int prec = TYPE_PRECISION (integer_type_node);
3413
3414 wide_int min = wi::shwi (minretval, prec);
3415 wide_int max = wi::shwi (maxretval, prec);
3416 set_range_info (lhs, VR_RANGE, min, max);
3417
3418 setrange = true;
3419 }
3420
3421 if (dump_file)
3422 {
3423 const char *inbounds
3424 = (minretval < info.objsize
3425 ? (maxretval < info.objsize
3426 ? "in" : "potentially out-of")
3427 : "out-of");
3428
3429 const char *what = setrange ? "Setting" : "Discarding";
3430 if (minretval != maxretval)
3431 fprintf (dump_file,
3432 " %s %s-bounds return value range [%llu, %llu].\n",
3433 what, inbounds,
3434 (unsigned long long)minretval,
3435 (unsigned long long)maxretval);
3436 else
3437 fprintf (dump_file, " %s %s-bounds return value %llu.\n",
3438 what, inbounds, (unsigned long long)minretval);
3439 }
3440 }
3441
3442 if (dump_file)
3443 fputc ('\n', dump_file);
3444
3445 return removed;
3446}
3447
3448/* Determine if a GIMPLE CALL is to one of the sprintf-like built-in
3449 functions and if so, handle it. Return true if the call is removed
3450 and gsi_next should not be performed in the caller. */
3451
3452bool
3453pass_sprintf_length::handle_gimple_call (gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi)
3454{
3455 call_info info = call_info ();
3456
3457 info.callstmt = gsi_stmt (*gsi);
3458 if (!gimple_call_builtin_p (info.callstmt, BUILT_IN_NORMAL))
3459 return false;
3460
3461 info.func = gimple_call_fndecl (info.callstmt);
3462 info.fncode = DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (info.func);
3463
3464 /* The size of the destination as in snprintf(dest, size, ...). */
3465 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT dstsize = HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U;
3466
3467 /* The size of the destination determined by __builtin_object_size. */
3468 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT objsize = HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U;
3469
3470 /* Buffer size argument number (snprintf and vsnprintf). */
3471 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT idx_dstsize = HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U;
3472
3473 /* Object size argument number (snprintf_chk and vsnprintf_chk). */
3474 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT idx_objsize = HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U;
3475
3476 /* Format string argument number (valid for all functions). */
3477 unsigned idx_format;
3478
3479 switch (info.fncode)
3480 {
3481 case BUILT_IN_SPRINTF:
3482 // Signature:
3483 // __builtin_sprintf (dst, format, ...)
3484 idx_format = 1;
3485 info.argidx = 2;
3486 break;
3487
3488 case BUILT_IN_SPRINTF_CHK:
3489 // Signature:
3490 // __builtin___sprintf_chk (dst, ost, objsize, format, ...)
3491 idx_objsize = 2;
3492 idx_format = 3;
3493 info.argidx = 4;
3494 break;
3495
3496 case BUILT_IN_SNPRINTF:
3497 // Signature:
3498 // __builtin_snprintf (dst, size, format, ...)
3499 idx_dstsize = 1;
3500 idx_format = 2;
3501 info.argidx = 3;
3502 info.bounded = true;
3503 break;
3504
3505 case BUILT_IN_SNPRINTF_CHK:
3506 // Signature:
3507 // __builtin___snprintf_chk (dst, size, ost, objsize, format, ...)
3508 idx_dstsize = 1;
3509 idx_objsize = 3;
3510 idx_format = 4;
3511 info.argidx = 5;
3512 info.bounded = true;
3513 break;
3514
3515 case BUILT_IN_VSNPRINTF:
3516 // Signature:
3517 // __builtin_vsprintf (dst, size, format, va)
3518 idx_dstsize = 1;
3519 idx_format = 2;
3520 info.argidx = -1;
3521 info.bounded = true;
3522 break;
3523
3524 case BUILT_IN_VSNPRINTF_CHK:
3525 // Signature:
3526 // __builtin___vsnprintf_chk (dst, size, ost, objsize, format, va)
3527 idx_dstsize = 1;
3528 idx_objsize = 3;
3529 idx_format = 4;
3530 info.argidx = -1;
3531 info.bounded = true;
3532 break;
3533
3534 case BUILT_IN_VSPRINTF:
3535 // Signature:
3536 // __builtin_vsprintf (dst, format, va)
3537 idx_format = 1;
3538 info.argidx = -1;
3539 break;
3540
3541 case BUILT_IN_VSPRINTF_CHK:
3542 // Signature:
3543 // __builtin___vsprintf_chk (dst, ost, objsize, format, va)
3544 idx_format = 3;
3545 idx_objsize = 2;
3546 info.argidx = -1;
3547 break;
3548
3549 default:
3550 return false;
3551 }
3552
3553 /* Set the global warning level for this function. */
3554 warn_level = info.bounded ? warn_format_trunc : warn_format_overflow;
3555
3556 /* The first argument is a pointer to the destination. */
3557 tree dstptr = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, 0);
3558
3559 info.format = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, idx_format);
3560
3561 /* True when the destination size is constant as opposed to the lower
3562 or upper bound of a range. */
3563 bool dstsize_cst_p = true;
3564
3565 if (idx_dstsize == HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U)
3566 {
3567 /* For non-bounded functions like sprintf, determine the size
3568 of the destination from the object or pointer passed to it
3569 as the first argument. */
3570 dstsize = get_destination_size (dstptr);
3571 }
3572 else if (tree size = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, idx_dstsize))
3573 {
3574 /* For bounded functions try to get the size argument. */
3575
3576 if (TREE_CODE (size) == INTEGER_CST)
3577 {
3578 dstsize = tree_to_uhwi (size);
3579 /* No object can be larger than SIZE_MAX bytes (half the address
3580 space) on the target.
3581 The functions are defined only for output of at most INT_MAX
3582 bytes. Specifying a bound in excess of that limit effectively
3583 defeats the bounds checking (and on some implementations such
3584 as Solaris cause the function to fail with EINVAL). */
3585 if (dstsize > target_size_max () / 2)
3586 {
3587 /* Avoid warning if -Wstringop-overflow is specified since
3588 it also warns for the same thing though only for the
3589 checking built-ins. */
3590 if ((idx_objsize == HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U
3591 || !warn_stringop_overflow))
3592 warning_at (gimple_location (info.callstmt), info.warnopt (),
3593 "specified bound %wu exceeds maximum object size "
3594 "%wu",
3595 dstsize, target_size_max () / 2);
3596 }
3597 else if (dstsize > target_int_max ())
3598 warning_at (gimple_location (info.callstmt), info.warnopt (),
3599 "specified bound %wu exceeds %<INT_MAX %>",
3600 dstsize);
3601 }
3602 else if (TREE_CODE (size) == SSA_NAME)
3603 {
3604 /* Try to determine the range of values of the argument
3605 and use the greater of the two at level 1 and the smaller
3606 of them at level 2. */
3607 wide_int min, max;
3608 enum value_range_type range_type
3609 = get_range_info (size, &min, &max);
3610 if (range_type == VR_RANGE)
3611 {
3612 dstsize
3613 = (warn_level < 2
3614 ? wi::fits_uhwi_p (max) ? max.to_uhwi () : max.to_shwi ()
3615 : wi::fits_uhwi_p (min) ? min.to_uhwi () : min.to_shwi ());
3616 }
3617
3618 /* The destination size is not constant. If the function is
3619 bounded (e.g., snprintf) a lower bound of zero doesn't
3620 necessarily imply it can be eliminated. */
3621 dstsize_cst_p = false;
3622 }
3623 }
3624
3625 if (idx_objsize != HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U)
3626 if (tree size = gimple_call_arg (info.callstmt, idx_objsize))
3627 if (tree_fits_uhwi_p (size))
3628 objsize = tree_to_uhwi (size);
3629
3630 if (info.bounded && !dstsize)
3631 {
3632 /* As a special case, when the explicitly specified destination
3633 size argument (to a bounded function like snprintf) is zero
3634 it is a request to determine the number of bytes on output
3635 without actually producing any. Pretend the size is
3636 unlimited in this case. */
3637 info.objsize = HOST_WIDE_INT_MAX;
3638 info.nowrite = dstsize_cst_p;
3639 }
3640 else
3641 {
3642 /* For calls to non-bounded functions or to those of bounded
3643 functions with a non-zero size, warn if the destination
3644 pointer is null. */
3645 if (integer_zerop (dstptr))
3646 {
3647 /* This is diagnosed with -Wformat only when the null is a constant
3648 pointer. The warning here diagnoses instances where the pointer
3649 is not constant. */
3650 location_t loc = gimple_location (info.callstmt);
3651 warning_at (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (dstptr, loc),
3652 info.warnopt (), "null destination pointer");
3653 return false;
3654 }
3655
3656 /* Set the object size to the smaller of the two arguments
3657 of both have been specified and they're not equal. */
3658 info.objsize = dstsize < objsize ? dstsize : objsize;
3659
3660 if (info.bounded
3661 && dstsize < target_size_max () / 2 && objsize < dstsize
3662 /* Avoid warning if -Wstringop-overflow is specified since
3663 it also warns for the same thing though only for the
3664 checking built-ins. */
3665 && (idx_objsize == HOST_WIDE_INT_M1U
3666 || !warn_stringop_overflow))
3667 {
3668 warning_at (gimple_location (info.callstmt), info.warnopt (),
3669 "specified bound %wu exceeds the size %wu "
3670 "of the destination object", dstsize, objsize);
3671 }
3672 }
3673
3674 if (integer_zerop (info.format))
3675 {
3676 /* This is diagnosed with -Wformat only when the null is a constant
3677 pointer. The warning here diagnoses instances where the pointer
3678 is not constant. */
3679 location_t loc = gimple_location (info.callstmt);
3680 warning_at (EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (info.format, loc),
3681 info.warnopt (), "null format string");
3682 return false;
3683 }
3684
3685 info.fmtstr = get_format_string (info.format, &info.fmtloc);
3686 if (!info.fmtstr)
3687 return false;
3688
3689 /* The result is the number of bytes output by the formatted function,
3690 including the terminating NUL. */
3691 format_result res = format_result ();
3692
3693 bool success = compute_format_length (info, &res);
3694
3695 /* When optimizing and the printf return value optimization is enabled,
3696 attempt to substitute the computed result for the return value of
3697 the call. Avoid this optimization when -frounding-math is in effect
3698 and the format string contains a floating point directive. */
3699 if (success
3700 && optimize > 0
3701 && flag_printf_return_value
3702 && (!flag_rounding_math || !res.floating))
3703 return try_substitute_return_value (gsi, info, res);
3704
3705 return false;
3706}
3707
3708/* Execute the pass for function FUN. */
3709
3710unsigned int
3711pass_sprintf_length::execute (function *fun)
3712{
3713 basic_block bb;
3714 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, fun)
3715 {
3716 for (gimple_stmt_iterator si = gsi_start_bb (bb); !gsi_end_p (si); )
3717 {
3718 /* Iterate over statements, looking for function calls. */
3719 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (si);
3720
3721 if (is_gimple_call (stmt) && handle_gimple_call (&si))
3722 /* If handle_gimple_call returns true, the iterator is
3723 already pointing to the next statement. */
3724 continue;
3725
3726 gsi_next (&si);
3727 }
3728 }
3729
3730 /* Clean up object size info. */
3731 fini_object_sizes ();
3732
3733 return 0;
3734}
3735
3736} /* Unnamed namespace. */

3738/* Return a pointer to a pass object newly constructed from the context
3739 CTXT. */
3740
3741gimple_opt_pass *
3742make_pass_sprintf_length (gcc::context *ctxt)
3743{
3744 return new pass_sprintf_length (ctxt);
3745}
